{"amendments":[{"body":"`src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:168-199` recomputes `MilestoneProgress` by counting every lineage row after `collapse_task_run_attempts`, but `collapse_task_run_attempts` in `src/contexts/milestone_record/model.rs:399-430` only merges legacy start/completion pairs, not separate retries. Since `MilestoneProgress` is documented as bead counts in `src/contexts/milestone_record/model.rs:191-205`, a bead that fails once and then succeeds on retry will persist `failed_beads=1` and `completed_beads=1` for that one bead. That makes `status.json` report historical attempts as current milestone state. The aggregation needs to collapse retries to one current state per bead, or store attempt-history counters separately from bead-progress counters.","rationale":"The new feature deliberately preserves retry history, so counting raw attempts in snapshot progress is now a correctness regression, not just a reporting quirk."}],"summary":"Reviewed the milestone lineage changes end-to-end in `src/contexts/milestone_record/model.rs`, `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs`, and `src/adapters/fs.rs`, and ran `cargo test --quiet` successfully. One correctness issue remains: snapshot progress aggregation now counts historical retry attempts as beads."}